<p>
    <strong>What is a bot?</strong>
    A bot is a software robot or a malware instance that runs autonomously on a compromised machine, often without being
    noticed by the victim user.
</p>

<p>
    <strong>A Botnet</strong>, also referred to as a <em>zombie army</em>,
    is the root cause of a large number of security problems on the internet; capable of large scale spamming, DDos attacks, data theft and fraud.
</p>

<p>
    <strong>Why do people create botnets?</strong>
<ul>
    <li>To profit financially</li>
    <li>To make a political or social statement</li>
    <li>To establish a name for themselves in the hacker community</li>
    <li>To celebrate some person or event</li>
    <li>To show companies how their systems are flawed</li>
    <li>Just because they can</li>

</ul>
